  "doc_id": "47349",
  "text": "Moreover, tenotomy can be \"dry\" (as a standalone procedure) or can be part of a combined intervention; i.e., associated with anaesthetics, corticosteroids, or regenerative products, such as blood or platelet-rich plasma (PRP). PRP consists of a plasma preparation with a concentration of platelets above peripheral blood (pure PRP) and optionally with concentrated leukocytes (L-PRP). The molecular pool present in PRP modulates biological processes involved in tissue healing, including modulation of angiogenesis and inflammation as well as cell proliferation and survival [CITATION_1] . In addition, it provides a fibrin template that can guide cells in the injured areas. Although these biological actions have been shown in vitro [CITATION_2] , the clinical efficacy of PRP preparations in tendons is still controversial.",
